Comedian Eric Omondi launched his studio, ‘Big Tym Entertainment’, on Tuesday in a private event attended by close friends and celebrities in Lavington. Speaking during the launch, Eric said providing a platform for all creatives across the region was a long-term dream he has had. "All my life I dreamt of an opportunity to showcase my craft to the world, but my biggest dream has always been to create a space for creatives," he said. "These studios are for every artiste, musician, comedians and actors to ensure maximum quality production for our corporate clients and partners." He added that the studios are in honour of legendary artistes. Present were Vioja Mahakami judge Lucy Wangui, Vitimbi’s Mama Kayai, Terence Creative and Chipukeezy.